      <div xml:id="NA87-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu (EV: talaivaṉ) varaiviṭai vaittup piriya āṟṟāḷāyt talaivi kaṉāk kaṇṭu tōḻikku uraittatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what SHE said to [her] confidante after having a dream, not bearing that [HE] would separate after the time for marriage had been fixed.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA87">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            uḷḷūr marāatta muḷeyiṟṟu vāva</l>
<l>            lōṅka lañciṉait tūṅkutuyil poḻutiṉ</l>
<l>            velpōrc cōḻa raḻiciyam peruṅkāṭṭu</l>
<l>            nelliyam puḷiccuvaik kaṉavi yāaṅ</l>
<l>            katukaḻin taṉṟē tōḻi yavarnāṭṭup </l>
<l>            paṉiyarum puṭainta peruntāṭ puṉṉai</l>
<l>            tuṟaimē yippi yīrmpuṟat tuṟaikkuñ</l>
<l>            ciṟukuṭi paratavar makiḻcciyum</l>
<l>            peruntaṇ kāṉalu niṉaintavap pakalē.</l>
        </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>It passed like a dream, friend,</l>
<l rend="indent">that has the sour taste of Nelli</l>
<l rend="indent2">from the great wildernes of Aḻici, the Cōḻa, victorious in battle,</l>
<l rend="indent3">at a time when the thorn-toothed bat from the tree</l>
<l rend="indent3">of the inner village is asleep, hanging on a high pretty branch,</l>
<l>– that day of thinking of the big cool seashore grove</l>
<l>and of the delight of the fishermen from the small hamlet,</l>
<l rend="indent">where large-trunked Puṉṉai trees,</l>
<l rend="indent">on which dewy buds have burst open,</l>
<l rend="indent">drip on the moist backs of the shells grazing the ghat</l>
<l rend="indent4">in his land.</l>
        </lg>
